 Q.   You seem to enjoy being back with Woody, you were with him as caddie for many a year, split up and now back in success again.   
SÃREN KJELDSEN:   We had six fantastic years, and then we just need a little bit of a break, and we had two years, and you realize sort of what you miss about the guy.   You know, I think he's perfect for me.   He's very calm.   He's got a great outlook on life, and I think, you know, for a caddie, you need a little bit of perspective.   Especially when the player isn't so happy and he thinks that the world depends on his golf game, because I certainly feel a bit like that sometimes, ridiculous as it may sound.   
But Kevin is so good with that, and he calms me down and he's got a massive influence on me.   
   
  
  
  
  
  

